1
00:00:27,827 --> 00:00:29,295
What are you here for?

2
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,401
An audit student of Han Eum Academy of Music.

3
00:00:37,137 --> 00:00:41,408
A Juilliard student is here to be
an audit student at Han Eum?

4
00:00:41,408 --> 00:00:42,609
Does that make sense?

5
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:46,412
We'll see each other often now,
so don't make that face.

6
00:00:57,357 --> 00:00:59,525
Hey, what's wrong?

7
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:06,733
It was the first time you
took me in your arms.

8
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:08,435
I did not.

9
00:01:08,435 --> 00:01:11,137
But you did. Like this.

10
00:01:12,281 --> 00:01:13,882
That's not it!

11
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:16,401
It's just...

12
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:20,296
Just... what?

13
00:01:26,339 --> 00:01:28,808
Stay here if you want.

14
00:01:30,290 --> 00:01:31,924
Hope to see you often!

15
00:01:33,693 --> 00:01:35,261
Sunbae!

16
00:01:35,261 --> 00:01:37,130
And I'll see you more often!

17
00:01:41,401 --> 00:01:44,070
They're definitely not dating.

18
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:47,682
But it won't be easy.

19
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:07,494
[Lesson 7]

20
00:02:07,494 --> 00:02:09,095
A Orchestra?

21
00:02:09,095 --> 00:02:11,264
It's the best orchestra
in the country.

22
00:02:11,264 --> 00:02:13,966
So it'll be good enough
for you, Yoon Hoo.

23
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:17,346
Isn't there another orchestra?

24
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:21,116
A special orchestra
that Maestro created...

25
00:02:21,116 --> 00:02:24,811
I heard Yoo Jin will
perform with them and

26
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,079
Maestro will conduct at the classical night.

27
00:02:27,613 --> 00:02:32,380
Then of course he'll perform
with the special orchestra.

28
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:36,381
You must be mistaken
about something.

29
00:02:36,381 --> 00:02:38,850
This performance is...

30
00:02:41,078 --> 00:02:44,314
We'll perform at the classical night, too.

31
00:02:48,007 --> 00:02:50,801
Are you going to conduct
this time, too?

32
00:02:50,801 --> 00:02:52,673
I won't be conducting this time.

33
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:54,341
Then who's conducting?

34
00:02:54,341 --> 00:02:56,643
Professor von Stresemann
will be conducting.

35
00:02:58,237 --> 00:03:02,007
I... will be playing the piano.

36
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:07,255
Hey, this... is not a dream, is it?

37
00:03:07,255 --> 00:03:09,439
The special orchestra that I'm
in as the bandmaster,

38
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:13,445
will be conducted by the world-famous maestro
and Cha Yoo Jin will perform together?

39
00:03:13,445 --> 00:03:16,154
Is this real or is this a dream?
Can someone pinch my cheek?

40
00:03:16,154 --> 00:03:17,555
- I will!
- I will!

41
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:26,798
Will we be on TV by any chance?

42
00:03:26,798 --> 00:03:29,526
It's a concert
by a world-famous maestro!

43
00:03:29,526 --> 00:03:32,421
- That's a possible!
- Professor von Stresemann!

44
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:35,374
We'll be really prepared for this.

45
00:03:35,374 --> 00:03:37,167
We don't want to get humiliated
in front of the whole country.

46
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:39,870
Of course!

47
00:03:44,189 --> 00:03:46,057
What is all this about?

48
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:54,260
Our genius!

49
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:56,528
I have a lesson with the professor.

50
00:03:57,456 --> 00:04:00,185
Well, if it's with the
maestro, I have no choice.

51
00:04:00,185 --> 00:04:01,867
You have to come
after the lesson.

52
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,922
- You have to come!
- Let's go! Let's go!

53
00:04:03,922 --> 00:04:06,191
Let's go!

54
00:04:06,806 --> 00:04:08,355
Let go of this!

55
00:04:16,034 --> 00:04:18,002
What the...
Why aren't you leaving?

56
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:22,803
I thought all night about
why you did that yesterday.

57
00:04:23,829 --> 00:04:24,863
About what?

58
00:04:24,863 --> 00:04:29,895
You took me in your arms
in front of the handsome cellist...

59
00:04:29,895 --> 00:04:31,396
I told you not to talk about that.

60
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:36,274
I'm sure it's because you don't like
me being with someone else.

61
00:04:36,274 --> 00:04:38,278
- That's not true.
- It is.

62
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,013
You're being jealous now.

63
00:04:40,539 --> 00:04:42,047
You're jealous!

64
00:04:42,047 --> 00:04:44,883
- You're jealous. Admit it!
- I'm not!

65
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:46,744
Go away!

66
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:50,658
[Han Eum Academy of Music]

67
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:02,735
I'm going to conduct A Orchestra, not S.

68
00:05:03,241 --> 00:05:04,567
Pardon?

69
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:05,969
Wait...

70
00:05:07,239 --> 00:05:08,873
Why is it A, and not S?

71
00:05:10,249 --> 00:05:13,552
My apprentice, have you gone deaf?

72
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:17,985
Our performance with A is already known

73
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:21,773
in the media and our school.

74
00:05:21,773 --> 00:05:25,001
Of course I assumed it would be S.

75
00:05:25,001 --> 00:05:26,621
Why didn't you tell me in advance?

76
00:05:27,672 --> 00:05:29,307
In advance?

77
00:05:30,998 --> 00:05:33,625
You didn't ask me.

78
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:35,761
We can still change it.

79
00:05:35,761 --> 00:05:38,589
You conducted at a workshop

80
00:05:38,589 --> 00:05:41,509
at Yoon Yi Song Music Festival
instead of me, right?

81
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:44,711
You should've known then...

82
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:48,781
about the joy of performing
with skilled musicians.

83
00:05:56,822 --> 00:06:00,527
Here! Eat all you want!

84
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:06,700
I brought digestive pills,
so eat everything here!

85
00:06:09,661 --> 00:06:13,557
My children will be performing
with a world-famous maestro...

86
00:06:13,557 --> 00:06:15,050
I'm so happy!

87
00:06:15,050 --> 00:06:16,418
Thank you, Father.

88
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:18,712
Don't mention it. I should thank you.

89
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:22,149
- Now, enjoy the food.
- Thank you!

90
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:28,013
But Sunbae is running late...

91
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:32,117
Once the practice starts,
Milch will have him all to himself.

92
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:36,271
My rival was Milch after all.

93
00:06:49,576 --> 00:06:55,815
I'm going to perform
with Orchestra A, not S.

94
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:12,282
Why did he leave his
cellphone off again?

95
00:07:13,016 --> 00:07:17,212
Did he forget about his mom?
He doesn't come here at all.

96
00:07:17,212 --> 00:07:20,481
Is he getting his revenge on me or what?

97
00:07:22,921 --> 00:07:26,257
He should keep himself
healthy before the concert.

98
00:07:28,824 --> 00:07:31,460
Mom, what brings you here?

99
00:07:33,996 --> 00:07:36,729
I was worried about you,
so I brought something good for you.

100
00:07:36,729 --> 00:07:38,797
But look what you're saying!

101
00:07:39,385 --> 00:07:41,045
I know we've been living apart
for a long time

102
00:07:41,045 --> 00:07:43,535
but can't you be
a little nicer to me?

103
00:07:43,535 --> 00:07:46,539
I came here because I was curious
if you were dead or alive!

104
00:07:46,539 --> 00:07:51,012
I'm only a stone's throw from here,
you could stop by on the way!

105
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:54,393
You're getting revenge on me
because you grew up by yourself, right?

106
00:07:54,393 --> 00:07:57,123
I told you that I don't need
you to take care of me.

107
00:07:58,061 --> 00:08:02,566
But that's too bad.
I want to give all that I can.

108
00:08:03,121 --> 00:08:04,981
I don't even have the right to do that?

109
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:09,114
I'm taking care of myself anyway.

110
00:08:09,114 --> 00:08:11,583
[What Nae Il wants to eat
Monday Pasta, Tuesday Steak...]

111
00:08:17,169 --> 00:08:19,833
There is still not even
a speck of dirt.

112
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,954
Being too clean is an illness.

113
00:08:21,954 --> 00:08:25,063
I got the illness from my
Mom who hated cleaning.

114
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:30,093
By the way... you really
came by just to bring me juice?

115
00:08:30,093 --> 00:08:33,096
No, I wanted to see you...

116
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:36,926
You have a girlfriend, right?

117
00:08:37,643 --> 00:08:39,545
I told you I broke up
with Do Kyung.

118
00:08:40,562 --> 00:08:44,566
Actually, it's more like raising her
than dating her.

119
00:08:44,566 --> 00:08:49,137
You brought home a wet dog in the rain
even though you're allergic to animal hair.

120
00:08:49,137 --> 00:08:50,269
What do you mean?

121
00:08:50,269 --> 00:08:51,895
I'm saying you're doing well.

122
00:08:51,895 --> 00:08:54,326
You had a barricade,
thinking about Viera everyday.

123
00:08:54,326 --> 00:08:58,330
But now you hang out with friends
at your age and became a conductor...

124
00:08:58,330 --> 00:09:00,884
I know your informants are everywhere.

125
00:09:00,884 --> 00:09:03,712
What about your friends?
Are you getting along?

126
00:09:03,712 --> 00:09:05,715
Are they nice to you?

127
00:09:05,715 --> 00:09:09,915
- Friends?
- The S Orchestra members.

128
00:09:09,915 --> 00:09:12,984
What?
Do you still just feel annoyed?

129
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,248
A little.

130
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,600
- Almighty Cha!
- Orabang!

131
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:21,186
- Almighty Cha!
- Of course kimchi stew is the best.

132
00:09:21,186 --> 00:09:24,350
- Have a bite!
- Almighty Cha!

133
00:09:24,350 --> 00:09:26,151
Don't follow me!

134
00:09:29,695 --> 00:09:32,989
Well, I'm not that annoyed.

135
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:34,573
They look like good kids.

136
00:09:34,573 --> 00:09:37,676
I'm thankful that they seem
to be really nice to you.

137
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,940
- Orabang! Wake up!
- Are you okay?

138
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:44,635
Orabang! Wake up, Orabang!

139
00:09:44,635 --> 00:09:47,404
Yoo Jin, are you okay?
Hey, Yoo Jin!

140
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:52,854
Yeah... it looks like they really mean it.

141
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:56,096
Isn't it really strange?

142
00:09:56,638 --> 00:10:01,520
How could they show everything
without hiding what they really want?

143
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:04,636
Do you think everyone keeps things
pressed down inside like you do?

144
00:10:04,636 --> 00:10:08,199
My mind will explode that way.
I can't live like that either!

145
00:10:08,199 --> 00:10:12,537
Because if I receive true friendship,
I have to return as much.

146
00:10:13,906 --> 00:10:16,742
I didn't think I'd have
time to return anything.

147
00:10:17,636 --> 00:10:19,871
Because I'll go study abroad.

148
00:10:22,456 --> 00:10:25,158
I didn't know my trauma
would last this long.

149
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:28,295
That's why I didn't take any.

150
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:34,218
But this time, I received that
true friendship before I knew it.

151
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,595
Yes, Mother.

152
00:10:45,243 --> 00:10:47,912
I plan to stay here for a while.

153
00:10:48,565 --> 00:10:51,969
I can't continue to stay at the hotel,
so I should look for a place to live.

154
00:10:53,028 --> 00:10:54,753
Of course.

155
00:10:54,753 --> 00:10:59,477
I'm wearing the finger brace
and getting finger treatments, too.

156
00:10:59,477 --> 00:11:01,870
Make sure to take care of yourself.

157
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,538
Okay.

158
00:11:18,804 --> 00:11:21,073
I'm asking you for the last time.

159
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:25,570
I'd like to perform with
S Orchestra this time.

160
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:32,116
I made it clear that
I'm performing with A.

161
00:11:32,116 --> 00:11:34,544
Without you and me...

162
00:11:34,544 --> 00:11:37,038
S Orchestra could really get dissolved.

163
00:11:37,038 --> 00:11:38,698
That's too bad.

164
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:41,352
You created that orchestra.

165
00:11:41,352 --> 00:11:44,547
Do you really believe that S Orchestra

166
00:11:44,547 --> 00:11:48,226
will carry out this
concert successfully?

167
00:11:48,226 --> 00:11:50,895
Make an objective decision.

168
00:11:50,895 --> 00:11:55,032
I'm sure you know better
about their capability.

169
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:59,118
Then I will...

170
00:12:00,523 --> 00:12:02,572
drop out of this performance.

171
00:12:06,643 --> 00:12:07,869
I'm sorry.

172
00:12:07,869 --> 00:12:10,004
Okay then.

173
00:12:11,523 --> 00:12:12,991
Professor?

174
00:12:18,614 --> 00:12:20,839
I'm glad Cha Yoo Jin is here, too.

175
00:12:20,839 --> 00:12:23,998
- The budget for the upcoming concert...
- There will be no concert.

176
00:12:23,998 --> 00:12:25,967
Cha Yoo Jin won't participate.

177
00:12:26,965 --> 00:12:28,533
What?

178
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:30,968
I'll get going now.

179
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:36,181
Cha Yoo Jin!

180
00:12:39,926 --> 00:12:42,513
Professor, what's going on?

181
00:12:42,513 --> 00:12:46,450
He can't give up on S Orchestra.

182
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:52,110
That's it?
You didn't try to convince him?

183
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:54,979
He said no, so why
should I convince him?

184
00:12:55,786 --> 00:12:59,551
Talents may be developed,
but geniuses are born.

185
00:12:59,551 --> 00:13:02,075
When a genius doesn't know his gift

186
00:13:02,075 --> 00:13:05,175
you have to make him fly by breaking
his legs, if that's what it takes.

187
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:08,687
When you respect
the student's freedom

188
00:13:08,687 --> 00:13:12,257
sitting aside means looking on,
not educating him.

189
00:13:17,422 --> 00:13:19,082
Hello, Chairwoman.

190
00:13:19,082 --> 00:13:21,519
I'll do what you told me to do before.

191
00:13:21,519 --> 00:13:25,956
We need to get rid of Professor von
Stresemann for the sake of school.

192
00:13:26,451 --> 00:13:29,420
I won't just sit by anymore.

193
00:13:30,037 --> 00:13:32,309
Just accept my conditions.

194
00:13:32,309 --> 00:13:35,779
Then I'll make Cha Yoo Jin perform, too.

195
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:40,003
We gave the news
to the media already,

196
00:13:40,003 --> 00:13:42,405
so we must make him
perform somehow.

197
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:49,863
I'll make sure to separate Cha Yoo Jin
from the losers this time.

198
00:13:58,881 --> 00:14:01,300
London Orchestra must be
awesome, Mini Min Hee.

199
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:04,470
I want to go see it, too.

200
00:14:05,512 --> 00:14:07,566
Ma Su Min! Mini Min Hee!

201
00:14:07,566 --> 00:14:10,893
- Are You already heading for practice?
- Of course.

202
00:14:10,893 --> 00:14:12,060
You've matured!

203
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:14,896
We could be on the news,
so we can't take it for granted.

204
00:14:14,896 --> 00:14:17,066
I'll be really strict from
now on, so get ready.

205
00:14:17,066 --> 00:14:19,860
I'm really going to practice hard,
even if I have to quit my part-time job.

206
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:22,540
- Practice hard!
- Mini Min Hee, I really like your mindset.

207
00:14:22,540 --> 00:14:25,509
You can have my dad's food for free instead!

208
00:14:26,908 --> 00:14:29,286
What about me?
I always practice hard.

209
00:14:29,286 --> 00:14:31,355
Then it's free for you, too!

210
00:14:32,664 --> 00:14:35,499
But keep it a secret
from other kids.

211
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:40,585
They're happy.

212
00:14:40,585 --> 00:14:42,212
What are they so happy about?

213
00:14:42,212 --> 00:14:45,748
Maybe they don't know that Professor and
Cha Yoo Jin are performing with us?

214
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:48,722
Jay Young, stop.

215
00:14:48,722 --> 00:14:50,246
Why?

216
00:14:50,891 --> 00:14:53,169
What do you mean?

217
00:14:53,169 --> 00:14:57,773
Maestro and Cha Yoo Jin
are performing with you?

218
00:15:06,671 --> 00:15:08,405
Cha Yoo Jin!

219
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:10,702
Yes, Professor.

220
00:15:10,702 --> 00:15:12,161
Excuse me.

221
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:14,946
You'll give up on this opportunity
because of those losers?

222
00:15:14,946 --> 00:15:17,626
You could get your name out
there in the world, but...

223
00:15:17,626 --> 00:15:19,168
I'm sorry.

224
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:20,921
You don't need to be sorry.

225
00:15:20,921 --> 00:15:24,188
The losers will pay
the price instead.

226
00:15:24,758 --> 00:15:27,261
Do you know about the complaint that
Yoon Yi Song Music Festival sent us?

227
00:15:27,261 --> 00:15:29,679
Seol Nae Il ran out on the first
day of the master class

228
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:32,235
and skipped the evaluation
without reason.

229
00:15:32,235 --> 00:15:35,179
That's never been seen or heard of
at Yoon Yi Song Music Festival.

230
00:15:36,019 --> 00:15:38,855
If you refuse to perform because of S Orchestra...

231
00:15:39,564 --> 00:15:42,818
I will notify the board of directors
about this right now

232
00:15:42,818 --> 00:15:45,196
and submit a proposition of dissolution.

233
00:15:50,174 --> 00:15:52,578
I only ask for once!

234
00:15:52,578 --> 00:15:56,473
If you just perform
this time for the school...

235
00:15:57,569 --> 00:16:01,572
then I'll give up
on the proposition as well.

236
00:16:09,701 --> 00:16:11,527
[Yoo Il Lak Idiot 2]

237
00:16:30,688 --> 00:16:32,857
What does this mean?

238
00:16:43,401 --> 00:16:45,102
That's Yoon Hoo!

239
00:16:45,870 --> 00:16:47,605
It's really Yoon Hoo.

240
00:16:55,599 --> 00:16:58,735
Hello, Mr. Cellist.

241
00:16:59,853 --> 00:17:02,556
But why are you here...

242
00:17:03,065 --> 00:17:05,234
You can just call me Yoon Hoo.

243
00:17:06,157 --> 00:17:07,825
I'm in this class, too.

244
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,194
We see each other pretty often.

245
00:17:11,194 --> 00:17:13,129
What an interesting coincidence.

246
00:17:14,284 --> 00:17:16,152
Would it be a coincidence?

247
00:17:17,141 --> 00:17:18,475
What?

248
00:17:25,212 --> 00:17:26,780
Lak?

249
00:17:27,351 --> 00:17:28,852
Hello?

250
00:17:29,466 --> 00:17:32,811
Lak, my class is about to start,
so be quick.

251
00:17:37,933 --> 00:17:39,334
What?

252
00:17:41,219 --> 00:17:45,788
No way. Why would Yoo Jin
perform with A, and not us?

253
00:17:47,484 --> 00:17:51,321
Okay, hang up for now.
Okay.

254
00:17:51,321 --> 00:17:54,305
- What do I do...
- Have a seat, everyone.

255
00:17:54,305 --> 00:17:56,910
I have someone I want to
introduce to you today.

256
00:17:56,910 --> 00:18:01,916
Professor, I'm sorry. I will be
a better student in the next class.

257
00:18:02,707 --> 00:18:04,461
Seol Nae Il!

258
00:18:09,006 --> 00:18:10,494
Mr. Lee Yoon Hoo.

259
00:18:10,494 --> 00:18:13,533
I'm sorry. She's a little odd.

260
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,220
Professor, I'm sorry.

261
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:17,889
I'll be a better student in the
next class, too.

262
00:18:29,901 --> 00:18:32,436
Let's get inside.

263
00:19:09,580 --> 00:19:12,850
It's just a rumor that
you'll be performing with A, right?

264
00:19:19,576 --> 00:19:22,873
See? It's just a rumor.

265
00:19:22,873 --> 00:19:25,209
Just practice for the concert.

266
00:19:26,798 --> 00:19:28,532
It's true.

267
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:35,425
It's true?

268
00:19:37,219 --> 00:19:38,919
Why does it have to be A Orchestra?

269
00:19:40,389 --> 00:19:43,050
It's the Han Eum orchestra,
the best in the

270
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,686
country with von Stresemann's conducting.

271
00:19:45,686 --> 00:19:48,066
Do you need more explanation?

272
00:19:48,066 --> 00:19:51,429
But, Almighty Cha, you said
you'd perform with us...

273
00:19:51,429 --> 00:19:55,906
I was mistaken. It was my mistake.

274
00:19:55,906 --> 00:19:59,324
And I'm not even your
official conductor.

275
00:19:59,324 --> 00:20:02,927
I'm just a temporary
conductor and a student.

276
00:20:05,873 --> 00:20:09,127
Yoo Jin, are you abandoning us
and leaving us?

277
00:20:09,127 --> 00:20:11,642
Do you have to go?
Can't you stay?

278
00:20:11,642 --> 00:20:13,505
Almighty Cha, can't you stay?

279
00:20:13,505 --> 00:20:15,040
Stop!

280
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:18,216
He said he wasn't going to stay.
He said he was leaving!

281
00:20:18,216 --> 00:20:20,584
Why are you hanging on to him?

282
00:20:21,847 --> 00:20:24,015
If you made your decision,
hurry up and leave.

283
00:20:29,487 --> 00:20:34,892
The applause at the last performance
was all about your skills.

284
00:20:40,282 --> 00:20:41,850
Sunbae!

285
00:20:47,357 --> 00:20:51,688
Sunbae, can't you just perform with us?

286
00:20:51,688 --> 00:20:53,649
You said you had fun
playing the duet with me

287
00:20:53,649 --> 00:20:56,076
and performing at the last concert.

288
00:20:56,076 --> 00:20:58,979
It'll be more fun if we
play together this time...

289
00:20:59,449 --> 00:21:01,618
I don't do music just to have fun.

290
00:21:02,095 --> 00:21:03,760
But, for me...

291
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:05,996
Why would I do that for you?

292
00:21:06,642 --> 00:21:08,301
What do you mean, why?

293
00:21:08,301 --> 00:21:11,224
I'm going to leave you
and stay with S Orchestra...

294
00:21:11,224 --> 00:21:13,459
This is a warning!

295
00:21:16,902 --> 00:21:18,370
Warning?

296
00:21:19,696 --> 00:21:25,601
Yes. I'm the mascot of S,
so I'm going to protect S.

297
00:21:26,957 --> 00:21:29,693
Right, you're the mascot.

298
00:21:30,415 --> 00:21:33,038
My brain keeps refusing the
fact, so I keep forgetting.

299
00:21:35,212 --> 00:21:38,882
So we're enemies from this moment, okay?

300
00:21:48,005 --> 00:21:50,241
See you at the concert!

301
00:21:54,356 --> 00:21:56,691
Why doesn't he look back...

302
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:07,138
So we're the only ones receiving the
support fund for the classical night?

303
00:22:07,138 --> 00:22:08,597
Of course.

304
00:22:08,597 --> 00:22:12,808
That's how it was allocated
in the beginning of the year.

305
00:22:12,808 --> 00:22:16,133
Well, there was no S then.

306
00:22:17,004 --> 00:22:20,274
Then... what's going to happen to S?

307
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:25,225
Cha Yoo Jin won't be there anymore.

308
00:22:25,225 --> 00:22:28,078
Now it's really the losers left there.

309
00:22:28,891 --> 00:22:31,927
They'll disperse on their own soon.

310
00:22:38,817 --> 00:22:41,452
Wait, wait!

311
00:22:41,452 --> 00:22:43,153
Where are you all going?

312
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:45,440
We have to decide on the music to perform.
We have a lot to do.

313
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:48,911
What can we do on our own without
Professor and Cha Yoo Jin?

314
00:22:48,911 --> 00:22:51,622
Even without Professor and Cha Yoo Jin,
I the bandmaster is here.

315
00:22:51,622 --> 00:22:53,290
Trust me.

316
00:22:55,873 --> 00:22:57,775
How can we trust you?

317
00:22:59,844 --> 00:23:01,048
I've lost my energy.

318
00:23:01,048 --> 00:23:03,642
Then is it over for us?

319
00:23:03,642 --> 00:23:05,886
What do you mean, 'is it over'?
I'm here.

320
00:23:05,886 --> 00:23:07,971
That's why it's over for us.

321
00:23:07,971 --> 00:23:10,473
It's just us, the losers.

322
00:23:37,668 --> 00:23:39,403
Hey, Yoo Jin!

323
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:46,303
Can't you... think it over one more time?

324
00:23:48,303 --> 00:23:51,272
Our conversation is over.
Nothing will change.

325
00:23:51,764 --> 00:23:55,602
You know, Yoo Jin...
Without you, we're really...

326
00:23:57,855 --> 00:24:00,644
We're losers...

327
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,735
So what?

328
00:24:04,735 --> 00:24:06,864
What does it have to do with me?

329
00:24:07,823 --> 00:24:10,158
We're so close...

330
00:24:14,496 --> 00:24:16,290
I wasn't going to say this

331
00:24:16,290 --> 00:24:17,726
but if you act this
way, you're forbidden

332
00:24:17,726 --> 00:24:19,376
from coming to the Mendelssohn.

333
00:24:19,376 --> 00:24:21,504
You won't get to eat
my father's food anymore.

334
00:24:26,175 --> 00:24:28,076
Yoo Jin...

335
00:24:29,511 --> 00:24:35,917
Okay... I will give you the
last chance as my best friend.

336
00:24:37,853 --> 00:24:40,556
Just think it over one more time.

337
00:24:45,129 --> 00:24:47,698
You're the only one
who think we're best friends.

338
00:24:50,407 --> 00:24:51,942
But not for me.

339
00:24:59,423 --> 00:25:01,826
I'm going to delete you
from my friend list.

340
00:25:02,377 --> 00:25:04,052
This is the last chance.

341
00:25:05,172 --> 00:25:08,375
Look at this! I'm really
going to delete you!

342
00:25:09,176 --> 00:25:11,745
Can you see this? I'm going to delete it!

343
00:25:13,514 --> 00:25:15,486
I'm really going to delete it!

344
00:26:25,335 --> 00:26:27,604
Sunbae, you're coming home now?

345
00:26:30,340 --> 00:26:32,049
Why are you here?

346
00:26:32,049 --> 00:26:34,553
I came to have dinner.

347
00:26:34,553 --> 00:26:36,887
But I guess you don't go
grocery shopping these days.

348
00:26:36,887 --> 00:26:38,996
The refrigerator is completely empty.

349
00:26:38,996 --> 00:26:40,965
Weren't we not seeing each other?

350
00:26:40,965 --> 00:26:42,866
You said we're at war.

351
00:26:45,969 --> 00:26:48,816
'Don't use separate rooms
even if you fight.'

352
00:26:48,816 --> 00:26:51,281
My mom told me
I won't lose out on anything

353
00:26:51,281 --> 00:26:53,840
as long as I listen to those
words from my ancestors.

354
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,280
Even if we're at war outside...

355
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:58,949
we could be on love mode inside...

356
00:26:59,493 --> 00:27:03,248
Cook for yourself if you have time
to look through my refrigerator.

357
00:27:03,916 --> 00:27:08,659
I'm hungry, so make something.
I'm really hungry.

358
00:27:08,659 --> 00:27:11,484
You become more shameless
everyday, Seol Nae Il.

359
00:27:17,262 --> 00:27:20,698
I'm doing a good job of
taking care of S Orchestra.

360
00:27:22,059 --> 00:27:24,728
I have a heavy responsibility.

361
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:30,768
Can't you at least do this for me?

362
00:27:33,423 --> 00:27:35,825
I told you it has nothing
to do with me.

363
00:27:36,949 --> 00:27:39,352
Olive pasta for dinner tonight.

364
00:27:40,244 --> 00:27:41,778
I have no pasta.

365
00:27:42,913 --> 00:27:44,498
Just eat steak.

366
00:27:44,498 --> 00:27:48,501
Steak? Really?
Hurry up please.

367
00:27:49,378 --> 00:27:51,947
I was so hungry...

368
00:27:52,603 --> 00:27:54,171
[Do Not Enter]

369
00:27:56,093 --> 00:27:58,971
It's our practice room.
What's going on, Professor?

370
00:27:58,971 --> 00:28:02,099
What orchestra when so
many members are leaving?

371
00:28:02,099 --> 00:28:03,641
They'll be all gone soon.

372
00:28:03,641 --> 00:28:05,225
We'll get new members.

373
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:08,686
Professor von Stresemann played you.
You still don't know?

374
00:28:08,686 --> 00:28:11,688
If he was going to take care of
you, he wouldn't perform with A!

375
00:28:12,436 --> 00:28:14,610
Just because you're in an orchestra,
it doesn't get you a job at the city orchestra.

376
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:16,194
Come to your senses!

377
00:28:16,194 --> 00:28:18,697
Don't waste your time being excited.

378
00:28:18,697 --> 00:28:20,885
Do you know the job placement
rate for music major graduates?

379
00:28:20,885 --> 00:28:22,665
Are you going to just hang
out and mess up your life?

380
00:28:22,665 --> 00:28:24,902
Do you have money or talent?

381
00:28:24,902 --> 00:28:28,272
If you have neither, come to your senses
and find your way to make a living.

382
00:28:30,586 --> 00:28:32,629
We have dreams, too.

383
00:28:32,629 --> 00:28:35,797
My dream is to become
a kindergarten teacher.

384
00:28:35,797 --> 00:28:37,968
And Lak will get a job at the city orchestra.

385
00:28:37,968 --> 00:28:40,818
And Mini Min Hee will set
up her own academy...

386
00:28:40,818 --> 00:28:42,833
- And...
- Stop.

387
00:28:44,194 --> 00:28:46,523
I can't go to the city orchestra at my level.

388
00:28:46,523 --> 00:28:49,138
- Lak!
- Il Lak...

389
00:29:33,815 --> 00:29:35,678
Stop please.

390
00:29:40,731 --> 00:29:44,586
You've never seduced anyone,
have you?

391
00:29:44,586 --> 00:29:45,635
Pardon?

392
00:29:45,635 --> 00:29:50,575
'I want to steal someone's glance',
'I want to capture those eyes'

393
00:29:50,575 --> 00:29:54,545
'I want to seduce her',
'I want to steal her heart.'

394
00:29:56,044 --> 00:29:58,696
You've never had that thought, have you?

395
00:29:58,696 --> 00:30:00,571
Well...

396
00:30:00,571 --> 00:30:04,234
You've probably
already caught their eyes...

397
00:30:05,442 --> 00:30:08,997
I guess you didn't
have to seduce anyone.

398
00:30:10,754 --> 00:30:12,521
Professor, what do you mean...

399
00:30:12,521 --> 00:30:14,089
Look.

400
00:30:25,701 --> 00:30:30,993
What do I look like right now?

401
00:30:35,043 --> 00:30:36,645
A snake...

402
00:30:37,588 --> 00:30:39,456
A serpent?

403
00:30:40,090 --> 00:30:41,925
It's seduction.

404
00:30:42,406 --> 00:30:49,646
It's the enchanting movement that
provokes and enamors the audience.

405
00:30:49,646 --> 00:30:52,184
Your movement just now?

406
00:30:52,184 --> 00:30:55,518
That's why your performance is boring.

407
00:30:55,518 --> 00:30:58,079
Do you listen to music
only with your ears?

408
00:30:58,079 --> 00:31:01,210
If sound is the only important thing
people can just buy CDs.

409
00:31:01,210 --> 00:31:03,304
Why would they come
to see the concert?

410
00:31:03,304 --> 00:31:09,932
Performers on stage have to
provoke and enamor the audience.

411
00:31:09,932 --> 00:31:16,706
You have to have the passion to steal
the ears and eyes of the audience.

412
00:31:16,706 --> 00:31:19,281
Like your gross...

413
00:31:21,271 --> 00:31:22,939
Odd movements?

414
00:31:24,676 --> 00:31:28,179
Again... with this feeling...

415
00:31:30,557 --> 00:31:34,392
We have a week until
the classical night.

416
00:31:34,879 --> 00:31:39,129
Wake your emotions up before that.

417
00:31:39,702 --> 00:31:41,103
Yes.

418
00:31:49,606 --> 00:31:51,119
Should I just take it off?

419
00:31:51,119 --> 00:31:54,024
We'll get dissolved for real then.

420
00:31:54,024 --> 00:31:56,994
I didn't have anywhere else to go.
I have no friends either.

421
00:31:57,459 --> 00:31:59,545
I was practicing with
the orchestra everyday.

422
00:31:59,545 --> 00:32:03,403
Me too. I was practicing and
working at the part-time job

423
00:32:03,403 --> 00:32:06,039
so I don't even know
my classmates' faces.

424
00:32:06,918 --> 00:32:09,129
We don't have much time
until the classical night.

425
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:13,370
I was planning
on a disguised orchestra.

426
00:32:13,370 --> 00:32:15,308
Disguised orchestra?

427
00:32:15,308 --> 00:32:18,902
It's visually noticeable...
That'll be really fun.

428
00:32:18,902 --> 00:32:21,275
- Right?
- Something like Rambo?

429
00:32:21,275 --> 00:32:23,944
It's totally off-the-wall.
It'll be a lot to watch.

430
00:32:23,944 --> 00:32:26,218
If we can... that'll be nice.

431
00:32:26,218 --> 00:32:29,199
My father said he'd come, too.

432
00:32:29,199 --> 00:32:31,614
But we have no money
and no conductor.

433
00:32:31,614 --> 00:32:33,649
We're not even good.

434
00:32:34,997 --> 00:32:37,158
Did we perform
because we were good?

435
00:32:37,158 --> 00:32:40,467
- We did it because it was fun.
- Right, we did it because it was fun!

436
00:32:40,467 --> 00:32:42,735
- Isn't it true?
- You're right!

437
00:32:43,546 --> 00:32:45,841
If we can just take that off...

438
00:32:45,841 --> 00:32:49,200
Then we can go in.
Lak, do something.

439
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:51,035
Figure out something.

440
00:32:55,873 --> 00:32:57,707
Aren't you going in?

441
00:33:05,736 --> 00:33:07,204
Look...

442
00:33:07,851 --> 00:33:09,079
I'm making this clear.

443
00:33:09,079 --> 00:33:12,100
You're the one who took off
the 'Do not enter' sign, Juilliard.

444
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:14,110
Yes, it's me.

445
00:33:18,290 --> 00:33:22,127
He probably doesn't know about
things because he's from abroad...

446
00:33:22,127 --> 00:33:23,921
Do you think it's okay?

447
00:33:23,921 --> 00:33:26,131
Since he's from Juilliard,
they'll go easy on him.

448
00:33:26,131 --> 00:33:27,466
But this is Han Eum.

449
00:33:27,466 --> 00:33:30,552
It's okay. If he gets kicked out,
he can go back to Juilliard.

450
00:33:30,552 --> 00:33:33,222
- Then what about us?
- You have no idea!

451
00:33:33,222 --> 00:33:35,424
Where do we go
if we get kicked out?

452
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:46,162
I received these orchestra
membership request forms.

453
00:33:46,162 --> 00:33:48,629
All of them canceled their
withdrawal from the membership...

454
00:33:50,489 --> 00:33:53,291
The one on top is my request form.

455
00:33:54,159 --> 00:33:57,162
S Orchestra won't last long anyway.

456
00:33:59,706 --> 00:34:01,344
Who knows.

457
00:34:03,126 --> 00:34:04,670
Do you think he really does
want to come in?

458
00:34:04,670 --> 00:34:07,433
- Ask him.
- Hurry up and ask him.

459
00:34:08,841 --> 00:34:11,329
You're really joining our orchestra?

460
00:34:11,329 --> 00:34:14,151
Yes. Only if you'd accept me.

461
00:34:16,479 --> 00:34:17,558
We're saved!

462
00:34:17,558 --> 00:34:20,355
A cello genius will be with us?

463
00:34:23,105 --> 00:34:27,023
You know... not anyone can
join our orchestra, right?

464
00:34:27,023 --> 00:34:31,069
I know... that this is Professor
von Stresemann's special orchestra.

465
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,696
That's right!

466
00:34:32,696 --> 00:34:36,285
Then it'll only be fair if
you have an entrance test.

467
00:34:36,285 --> 00:34:38,912
- Lak!
- Test?

468
00:34:38,912 --> 00:34:42,107
- With Lee Yoon Hoo? Are you crazy?
- I have to just stuff your mouth!

469
00:34:42,107 --> 00:34:43,775
Stop it really!

470
00:35:40,837 --> 00:35:42,575
Cha Yoo Jin!

471
00:35:43,186 --> 00:35:45,655
Where are you going?
We'll start our practice soon.

472
00:35:46,813 --> 00:35:47,880
Right.

473
00:35:48,855 --> 00:35:50,734
It became a habit.

474
00:36:20,711 --> 00:36:23,213
Bravo!

475
00:36:25,352 --> 00:36:27,788
We just need to practice!

476
00:36:37,823 --> 00:36:40,284
We're really saved now!

477
00:36:40,284 --> 00:36:45,747
I couldn't go to A Orchestra...
and I can't play timpani alone...

478
00:36:45,747 --> 00:36:47,875
I was really lost.

479
00:36:47,875 --> 00:36:50,769
We just need to find a conductor now.
We'll be fine.

480
00:36:50,769 --> 00:36:54,727
I wish a conductor would
drop from the sky.

481
00:36:54,727 --> 00:36:57,563
Please! Drop one please!

482
00:37:00,457 --> 00:37:03,459
You guys are looking for a conductor?

483
00:37:05,225 --> 00:37:07,694
I have a bit of free time these days...

484
00:37:09,559 --> 00:37:11,119
- Should I do You a favor?
- Really?

485
00:37:11,119 --> 00:37:13,455
- Really?
- Seriously?

486
00:37:13,455 --> 00:37:14,698
Is this really happening?

487
00:37:14,698 --> 00:37:16,766
Cellist Lee Yoon Hoo.

488
00:37:17,237 --> 00:37:19,320
Right?

489
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:21,471
You really joined S?

490
00:37:21,471 --> 00:37:24,325
We listen to his performance today,
and let him join as a special case.

491
00:37:24,325 --> 00:37:27,122
Thank you... for accepting me.

492
00:37:27,122 --> 00:37:29,956
Friend, where have you been all this time?

493
00:37:29,956 --> 00:37:32,949
Let's go together forever.
Our friendship won't change.

494
00:37:32,949 --> 00:37:35,547
We just need to practice
until the classical night.

495
00:37:35,547 --> 00:37:37,839
Practice! Practice! Let's go!

496
00:37:37,839 --> 00:37:40,260
Let's go! Let's go practice! Now!

497
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:42,346
Let's go practice!

498
00:37:42,346 --> 00:37:44,461
Wait for me. Wait for me!

499
00:37:44,461 --> 00:37:47,564
The losers became something.

500
00:37:52,022 --> 00:37:56,126
Do you think S Orchestra
will do well without Cha Yoo Jin?

501
00:37:56,921 --> 00:38:00,357
They can get up on their own.

502
00:38:01,724 --> 00:38:05,469
You've always been so mean, Franz.

503
00:38:05,469 --> 00:38:10,507
It's time for me to be mean.
They have to go through this anyway.

504
00:38:11,208 --> 00:38:13,920
Especially for Cha Yoo Jin.

505
00:38:16,421 --> 00:38:18,790
At the upcoming concert...

506
00:38:20,603 --> 00:38:24,766
please watch us from the front seat.

507
00:38:24,766 --> 00:38:27,531
Of course. I'm the dean.

508
00:38:28,141 --> 00:38:33,179
Please listen, not as the
dean, but as Mina.

509
00:38:33,728 --> 00:38:42,739
My true feelings for you that I didn't
get to deliver a long time ago...

510
00:38:44,408 --> 00:38:46,443
I'll put it in this concert.

511
00:38:47,170 --> 00:38:49,431
What do you mean by that...

512
00:38:49,431 --> 00:38:54,235
I forgot about some documents,
so I have to get going.

513
00:38:56,092 --> 00:38:57,694
Bye now.

514
00:39:04,344 --> 00:39:08,447
I have no time to postpone anymore.

515
00:39:27,451 --> 00:39:29,620
Wait. Wait!

516
00:39:30,871 --> 00:39:33,537
You shouldn't cut off like that there.

517
00:39:33,537 --> 00:39:36,293
Just reduce the sound a little...

518
00:39:36,293 --> 00:39:41,349
'Dolce, ' soft and sweet. 'Legato.'

519
00:39:42,731 --> 00:39:47,636
Chae Do Kyung, it looks like you've
gotten worse after the audition.

520
00:40:01,860 --> 00:40:05,063
You don't look so good.
Are you not feeling well?

521
00:40:07,324 --> 00:40:08,925
I'm fine.

522
00:40:11,888 --> 00:40:15,283
It's not a lesson,
so it should be okay.

523
00:40:15,283 --> 00:40:18,249
Then are you hungry? Do you
want something to drink?

524
00:40:18,249 --> 00:40:22,256
The boss told me to get you anything
you want when you're practicing.

525
00:40:22,985 --> 00:40:25,126
You have to have a full
stomach to play well.

526
00:40:25,126 --> 00:40:27,590
I'm okay for now.

527
00:40:29,888 --> 00:40:32,221
It's almost time to perform.

528
00:40:32,221 --> 00:40:35,143
Mini Min Hee, do you have
any music you want to hear?

529
00:40:36,598 --> 00:40:38,895
I have! 'Love Dream.'

530
00:40:42,025 --> 00:40:46,296
Okay, okay. Here comes
'Love Dream' for Mini Min Hee.

531
00:40:47,911 --> 00:40:50,780
One, two, three.

532
00:41:30,532 --> 00:41:32,784
- Mother.
- Do Kyung!

533
00:41:32,784 --> 00:41:34,286
You're here often.

534
00:41:34,286 --> 00:41:35,910
Are you tired of me?

535
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:38,595
No way. I'm glad to see you.

536
00:41:38,595 --> 00:41:40,897
I came to give you something.

537
00:41:42,208 --> 00:41:46,632
It's a CD of Contini's live
piano recital in Milan.

538
00:41:47,171 --> 00:41:50,216
This must have been
really hard to find.

539
00:41:50,216 --> 00:41:52,593
This should be helpful to Yoo Jin.

540
00:41:52,593 --> 00:41:55,933
Please give it to him for me.

541
00:42:00,784 --> 00:42:03,987
Sure, thank you for being
so thoughtful.

542
00:42:04,525 --> 00:42:07,236
You have a performance
on the classical night too, right?

543
00:42:07,236 --> 00:42:08,779
Yes.

544
00:42:08,779 --> 00:42:11,490
Actually, I was interviewed
by 'Classical Monthly'

545
00:42:11,490 --> 00:42:14,824
as part of the Han Eum special feature.

546
00:42:14,824 --> 00:42:17,829
The magazine that interviewed
Yoo Jin recently.

547
00:42:20,870 --> 00:42:22,705
That girl...

548
00:42:24,126 --> 00:42:26,995
must have a part-time job
playing the piano here.

549
00:42:29,049 --> 00:42:30,759
You're still the same.

550
00:42:30,759 --> 00:42:33,256
I was curious
since she played a duet with him.

551
00:42:33,256 --> 00:42:35,211
She's cute.

552
00:42:35,211 --> 00:42:37,520
Yoo Jin also seems to find her cute.

553
00:42:38,202 --> 00:42:39,557
I see.

554
00:42:40,857 --> 00:42:44,494
Yoo Jin is surprisingly good
at taking care of people.

555
00:42:59,542 --> 00:43:02,878
Nae Il, Chae Do Kyung is here again.

556
00:43:03,726 --> 00:43:06,829
She must be going on well
with the boss's son.

557
00:43:08,063 --> 00:43:10,933
I was a little nervous because
she's the ex-girlfriend...

558
00:43:11,434 --> 00:43:15,590
But now I can be a little bit at ease
about Yoo Jin. Right, Mini Min Hee?

559
00:43:15,590 --> 00:43:17,440
I don't know.

560
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:19,889
I don't want to hear about Yoo Jin.

561
00:43:19,889 --> 00:43:21,475
Mini Min Hee...

562
00:43:23,059 --> 00:43:24,560
Hey!

563
00:43:50,693 --> 00:43:52,915
Yoon Hoo...

564
00:43:52,915 --> 00:43:55,084
It looks like
you're avoiding someone.

565
00:43:55,795 --> 00:43:57,681
Are you a runaway?

566
00:43:58,388 --> 00:44:00,515
It's Professor Ahn.

567
00:44:00,515 --> 00:44:03,985
I haven't been taking lessons
recently, so he's a little upset.

568
00:44:04,643 --> 00:44:06,928
You like playing the piano.

569
00:44:06,928 --> 00:44:08,357
So why do you miss the lessons?

570
00:44:08,357 --> 00:44:12,237
I still like playing the piano.
I have a part-time job, too.

571
00:44:12,817 --> 00:44:16,243
But... as for taking lessons...

572
00:44:17,033 --> 00:44:20,606
Miss Seol Nae Il!
Where did you lose your mind?

573
00:44:21,912 --> 00:44:23,820
Are you kidding me?

574
00:44:28,210 --> 00:44:33,617
Well... there was a time
that I hated cello so much.

575
00:44:33,617 --> 00:44:35,872
But you're doing well now.

576
00:44:37,177 --> 00:44:38,882
Because I met someone.

577
00:44:40,590 --> 00:44:45,661
I met a pianist that I really
wanted to perform with.

578
00:44:48,185 --> 00:44:53,026
If you meet someone like that,
you'll want to start taking lessons again.

579
00:44:53,026 --> 00:44:55,839
I hope that happens.

580
00:45:31,273 --> 00:45:33,233
You took care of it well, didn't you?

581
00:45:33,233 --> 00:45:35,827
Bring out the tune more, Viola.

582
00:45:35,827 --> 00:45:38,789
- Timpani, with more energy.
- That's my specialty.

583
00:45:38,789 --> 00:45:42,518
Don't get too hung up on vibrato.
You have good feelings.

584
00:45:42,518 --> 00:45:44,896
Nae Il, let's go!

585
00:45:45,579 --> 00:45:48,359
- Make sure to keep your position.
- Yes.

586
00:45:52,127 --> 00:45:53,695
Who is it?

587
00:45:55,172 --> 00:45:56,874
It's Milch.

588
00:46:01,591 --> 00:46:05,807
You told me that you'd introduce me
to a student who played 'eroica' today.

589
00:46:05,807 --> 00:46:09,671
If you're joking again,
I won't let it slide this time.

590
00:46:10,562 --> 00:46:13,332
I called her to come here.

591
00:46:16,151 --> 00:46:18,152
She's here.

592
00:46:18,842 --> 00:46:20,643
Baby...

593
00:46:25,008 --> 00:46:26,843
Hello.

594
00:46:32,689 --> 00:46:34,140
You can't be...

595
00:46:35,013 --> 00:46:37,526
talking about this student, can you?

596
00:46:38,728 --> 00:46:40,409
I am.

597
00:46:41,301 --> 00:46:47,640
Baby is the pianist that you
were looking for, Professor Do.

598
00:46:56,066 --> 00:46:58,868
Do you hate me that much?

599
00:46:58,868 --> 00:47:00,803
I don't hate you.

600
00:47:06,827 --> 00:47:08,328
Seriously...

601
00:47:14,334 --> 00:47:17,379
Milch, what's going on with him?

602
00:47:17,379 --> 00:47:19,843
Oh, Baby...

603
00:48:01,670 --> 00:48:03,199
Sunbae!

604
00:48:06,553 --> 00:48:08,621
I told you to ignore him.

605
00:48:09,632 --> 00:48:13,267
He left us because he didn't like us.
Why would you say hello to him?

606
00:48:15,896 --> 00:48:17,230
Let's go.

607
00:48:26,395 --> 00:48:29,999
Almighty Cha... see you next time.

608
00:48:52,808 --> 00:48:55,844
This is strange.
Why isn't he picking it up?

609
00:49:02,638 --> 00:49:04,303
Sunbae.

610
00:49:11,314 --> 00:49:13,816
Sunbae, are you inside?

611
00:49:18,453 --> 00:49:21,856
That's strange. Where is he?

612
00:50:24,399 --> 00:50:26,501
Is he still not home yet?

613
00:50:28,946 --> 00:50:31,248
Did he go to school to practice?

614
00:50:33,617 --> 00:50:35,585
He should take care of himself...

615
00:51:41,143 --> 00:51:42,443
Are you okay?

616
00:51:43,825 --> 00:51:46,194
- You don't look good at all...
- Don't touch me!

617
00:51:51,820 --> 00:51:55,623
You have... stage fright, right?

618
00:51:57,293 --> 00:52:01,085
- Can you get on the podium like this?
- Of course. Who do You think I am?

619
00:52:01,085 --> 00:52:02,885
I can do it.

620
00:52:02,885 --> 00:52:07,055
I didn't see Cha Yoo Jin perform
so I have no one to compare this time.

621
00:52:07,055 --> 00:52:08,757
So...

622
00:52:13,467 --> 00:52:14,974
What do I do?

623
00:52:15,511 --> 00:52:16,944
I can't do it.

624
00:52:27,689 --> 00:52:29,251
It's okay.

625
00:52:30,612 --> 00:52:32,861
Anyone can get stage fright.

626
00:52:32,861 --> 00:52:36,747
What about the performance?

627
00:52:44,413 --> 00:52:47,048
You saw, right? Everyone's eyes...

628
00:52:47,048 --> 00:52:48,542
We've got their attention for sure.

629
00:52:48,542 --> 00:52:51,836
I think they'll come to see us
even just out curiosity, Sunbae.

630
00:52:51,836 --> 00:52:53,505
We're the best!

631
00:52:59,888 --> 00:53:02,599
Mini Min Hee, what do you think of my costume?

632
00:53:02,599 --> 00:53:04,374
You're totally cute, Nae Il.

633
00:53:04,374 --> 00:53:06,228
Mini Min Hee, you're pretty too!

634
00:53:06,228 --> 00:53:08,370
You were sewing for days...

635
00:53:08,370 --> 00:53:09,738
And it's a raccoon after all?

636
00:53:09,738 --> 00:53:11,936
Isn't it cute? Don't I
look like the mascot?

637
00:53:11,936 --> 00:53:14,972
Yes, you're so cute that I want to
give you a little knuckle jab.

638
00:53:17,614 --> 00:53:19,462
I think it's time.

639
00:53:19,462 --> 00:53:21,608
Everyone, let's go rehearse!

640
00:53:26,832 --> 00:53:30,306
By the way, the conductor...

641
00:53:30,306 --> 00:53:32,241
Where is Seung Ho?

642
00:53:33,422 --> 00:53:36,558
- Did you see him, Min Hee?
- I didn't see him.

643
00:53:51,732 --> 00:53:55,482
Han Seung Ho is sick and
went to the hospital.

644
00:53:55,482 --> 00:53:56,778
What?

645
00:53:56,778 --> 00:53:59,710
- Then what about us?
- What do we do?

646
00:54:04,333 --> 00:54:07,080
Mini Min Hee, my cellphone is in my bag.

647
00:54:07,080 --> 00:54:09,815
Take it out and send a text message
to Yoo Jin Sunbae please.

648
00:54:10,513 --> 00:54:13,582
Send a text message to Yoo Jin?

649
00:54:14,088 --> 00:54:15,532
Yes...

650
00:54:15,532 --> 00:54:19,021
Since I'm getting
ready now, so please.

651
00:54:19,607 --> 00:54:22,394
If he comes for us...

652
00:54:22,394 --> 00:54:24,447
We'll be grateful.

653
00:54:24,447 --> 00:54:26,266
Then we'll be able to perform.

654
00:54:26,266 --> 00:54:28,852
So send a text to Sunbae.

655
00:54:28,852 --> 00:54:31,454
If he comes, no one
will be upset anymore.

656
00:55:12,184 --> 00:55:14,347
What do we do, Sunbae?

657
00:55:14,347 --> 00:55:17,713
We're about to perform
without a conductor.

658
00:55:19,444 --> 00:55:21,312
What does she want me to do...

659
00:55:23,615 --> 00:55:26,243
Did you really send a text to Sunbae?

660
00:55:26,243 --> 00:55:27,823
I did.

661
00:55:27,823 --> 00:55:29,371
Then why is he not coming?

662
00:55:29,371 --> 00:55:31,106
He'll come, right?

663
00:55:32,127 --> 00:55:33,795
Hey...

664
00:55:34,443 --> 00:55:36,291
We'll start soon, so we should go.

665
00:55:36,291 --> 00:55:37,566
Yes.

666
00:55:37,566 --> 00:55:39,201
Let's go.

667
00:55:43,226 --> 00:55:45,494
Why isn't he coming?

668
00:56:11,997 --> 00:56:15,400
Cha Yoo Jin! Where are you going?
We have a rehearsal!

669
00:56:17,586 --> 00:56:20,889
What's going on, Seol Nae Il?
Answer the phone!

670
00:56:32,935 --> 00:56:35,404
Are you planning to perform
without a conductor?

671
00:56:59,761 --> 00:57:02,555
Tuning a melodeon?

672
00:57:03,465 --> 00:57:04,933
Seol Nae Il?

673
00:57:05,714 --> 00:57:09,578
It's 'Mambo' by Leonard Bernstein.

674
00:59:06,421 --> 00:59:08,131
They are good.

675
00:59:08,131 --> 00:59:10,467
It's not just the good ones.

676
00:59:10,467 --> 00:59:12,618
They have perfect harmony.

677
00:59:12,618 --> 00:59:15,264
They probably didn't have
time to practice together...

678
00:59:15,264 --> 00:59:17,128
Is this possible?

679
00:59:49,548 --> 00:59:52,516
Bravo! Bravo!

680
00:59:55,470 --> 00:59:57,631
What are you doing here
before our concert?

681
00:59:57,631 --> 01:00:01,834
What are you doing here,
not at the rehearsal as the pianist?

682
01:00:03,886 --> 01:00:06,356
What a great performance.

683
01:00:06,356 --> 01:00:09,258
Of course, it's Lee Yoon Hoo!

684
01:00:10,360 --> 01:00:14,264
He knows how to
capture people's hearts.

685
01:00:16,950 --> 01:00:21,721
He got the members
on his side already.

686
01:00:24,958 --> 01:00:27,252
Let's go do our concert now.

687
01:00:27,252 --> 01:00:30,789
This is a special day
for me as well.

688
01:00:41,509 --> 01:00:42,991
It was great.

689
01:00:42,991 --> 01:00:45,768
Yes, it was fun.

690
01:00:45,768 --> 01:00:47,720
But this is it.

691
01:00:49,411 --> 01:00:52,948
The star of the day is... me.

692
01:01:26,812 --> 01:01:31,217
If you're embarrassed to show
your feelings, you won't grow anymore.

693
01:01:31,217 --> 01:01:32,872
You guys were great.

694
01:01:32,872 --> 01:01:34,337
That was awesome.

695
01:01:34,337 --> 01:01:37,406
I heard the fan who changes
his heart will be the meanest anti-fan.

696
01:01:37,406 --> 01:01:38,782
What did you do?

697
01:01:38,782 --> 01:01:41,820
- It'll be difficult to bear...
- I will!

698
01:01:41,820 --> 01:01:43,713
Professor von Stresemann got dragged out?

699
01:01:43,713 --> 01:01:44,955
Why? By whom?

700
01:01:44,955 --> 01:01:47,875
It's not because of you.
It's me.

701
01:01:47,875 --> 01:01:54,281
I am a little... this tiny bit proud of you.
